  <h2>The Cost Variables</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Repair versus replacement.</strong> Restoring function is a different scope than designing and installing a new field.</li>
    <li><strong>Soil and site conditions.</strong> The ground itself drives what is possible and how much excavation is involved.</li>
    <li><strong>Access and restoration.</strong> Reaching the field and restoring the property afterward both factor in.</li>
    <li><strong>Design and approvals.</strong> A replacement field involves planning appropriate to the site.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why Maintenance Pays Off</h2>
  <p>
    Because this is the expensive end of septic ownership, routine <a href="/resources/septic-pumping-maintenance/">pumping and maintenance</a> is the cheapest protection you have. If you are seeing field symptoms, <a href="/request-service/">request septic service</a> for an evaluation before the situation grows.
  </p>

